<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
Perennial herb, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" unit="m" value="0.6">0.6 m</quantity>
in height. Basal leaves 50-100
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.0" unit="mm" value="27.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="20.0">20-35 mm</quantity>
, lanceolate-elliptic shaped, softly hairy, deciduous, margins entire. Stem leaves 40-100
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.9" unit="mm" value="14.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="9.0">9-20 mm</quantity>
, lanceolate shaped, apex acute, base cuneate, entire margins, densely covered with white brittle hairs. Trichomes soft, upright, bulbous based. Inflorescence clustered at the apex, pedicels 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5-8 mm</quantity>
long, lengthens considerably in fruit. Calyx ca. 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long, lobes ovate, grey pubescent, apex subacute. Corolla bluish purple; lobe 7
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
diameter, segments round. Nutlets ovoid, 2-4
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3-4 mm</quantity>
, convex shaped; glochidia short, thick, marginal glochidia are more distinct than the central glochidia (Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Cynoglossum amabile. SEM micrograph of the adaxial surface of A fruit nutlets B Glochidia. Voucher specimen: J. Stewart 2021 (NU). SEM images scale bar: 2 mm (A); 100 µm (B)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.193.72270.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/658889" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
